The widow of the late award-winning music producer Robbie Malinga, Ann shared on her Instagram page that she woke up missing him. She wrote a short and sweet message that read: “Woke up missing my forever.” The message was accompanied by a heart emoji. The star passed away after a short illness in 2017. The musician might be gone but he is still remembered by many people and his fans. Robbie produced hits like Lilizela Mzansi, African Love Story and Baby Please. He also unearthed many talents during his time. Robbie also worked with the likes of Kelly Khumalo, Musa Sukwene, Naima Kay, and Vusi Nova. Together they produced smash hits that made South African music lovers lose their minds and enjoyed their festive seasons to good sound. 